com.github.daytron.daytronmoney.currency

Class Money

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.daytron.daytronmoney.currency.Money

  • public final class Money
extends Object
    Class that represents a single monetary value. This is an immutable class, its value cannot be changed. All operation output returns a new object of this class.
    Author:
    Ryan Gilera

        public Money(long wholeUnit)

        Parameters:

      • Money

        public Money()
        Creates a new Money object that takes no arguments, value represents as zero. Currency code is set to default local currency code. Leading decimal zeroes is set to zero. Sign is set to positive. Whole and decimal unit is set to zero.
